'''Gordon Bennett''' is an expression that is used to denote surprise or shock. A typical usage, for instance, might be "Gordon Bennett! Look at the size of that." It is a common expression or exclamation used in [[British English]], and there is a comic book character, [[Gordon Bennett (character)|Gordon Bennett]], based on the expression. 

[[James Gordon Bennett, Jr.|James Gordon Bennett, Junior]] inspired the expression.
Bennett &mdash; the son of [[James Gordon Bennett, Sr.|James Gordon Bennett, Senior]] &mdash; was a notorious [[New York]] [[newspaper]] proprietor and [[Playboy (disambiguation)|playboy]] during the late 19th and early 20th centuries, who became famous for his extravagant lifestyle and behaviour. For example, James Gordon Bennett, Jr once arrived late and drunk at a party, at the mansion of the family of his fiancee, socialite [[Caroline May]].  Once there, he urinated into the fireplace in full view of his hosts.  The engagement was broken off immediately, and the subsequent notoriety caused Bennett to move to [[France]].  This incident has appeared in the ''[[Guinness Book of World Records]]'', under "Greatest Engagement [[Faux Pas]]." 

As a result of such incidents, "Gordon Bennett" became stuck in the British [[vernacular]].

